HEADWORD: oddity
<hw>odd"i*ty</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Oddities</plw>
<pr>(⟦ocr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being odd; singularity; queerness; peculiarity; <as>as,
<ex>oddity</ex> of dress, manners, and the like</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That infinitude of <qex>oddities</qex> in him.</q>
<rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is odd; <as>as, a collection of
<ex>oddities</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>odd-job</ent>⟦br⟧
